Style.content: Changes that o not affect the meaning of the code (whit-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc).

Refactor.content: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.

Perf.content: A code change that improves performance.

Test.content: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests.

Build.content: Changes that affect the builda system or external dependencies (examples escopes: gulp, brocoli, npm).

CI.content: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts (example scopes: Travis, Circle, BrowserStack, SauceLabs).

Chore.content: Other changes that don't modify src or test files.
